<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1567,2004]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1567,1593]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Plate short, 0.6–0.7 times as long as maximum width; lateral margin with a right-angled step medially; posterior margin truncate, or somewhat triangular (
<figureCitation box="[899,972,1605,1631]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="57.[151,255,1711,1735]" captionTargetBox="[198,1389,205,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-63@57.[190,1396,194,1718]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURE 2 a–i. Pravistylus species. Plate, part or whole structure. a, P. varicudiscus sp. n.; b, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; c, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; d, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; e–g, P.eductus(Naudé); h–i, P. exquadratus (Naudé)." pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
aq). Aedeagal shaft short, tubular, Ushaped in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[423,516,1642,1668]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="62.[151,255,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[249,1353,187,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-126@62.[233,1361,182,1903]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 3 a–t. Pravistylus species. Aedeagus, laterally. a–b, P.lobus sp. n.; c, P. deltoplacussp. n.; d, P. mecophysis sp. n.; e, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; f, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; g, P. mollidiscus sp. n.; h, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; i–k, P. mutilidiscus sp. n.; l, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; m, P. odontiophallus sp. n.; n–o, P.eductus (Naudé); p–q, P. exquadratus (Naudé); r, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; s, P. macropygeus sp. n.; t, P. pollediscus sp. n." pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Figs 3 f</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[528,563,1642,1668]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="64.[151,255,1673,1697]" captionTargetBox="[188,1400,199,1606]" captionTargetId="figure-144@64.[181,1405,194,1694]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURE 4 a–q. Pravistylus species. Aedeagus, dorsally or ventrally. a, P. lobus sp. n., dorsal; b, P. lobus sp. n., ventral; c, P. deltoplacus sp. n., dorsal; d, P. mecophysis sp. n., dorsal; e, P. bidentidiscus sp. n., dorsal; f, P. brachyplacus sp. n., dorsal; g, P. mollidiscus sp. n., dorsal; h, P. mecistoplacus sp. n., dorsal; i, P. mutilidiscus sp. n., dorsal; j, P. brachyphysis sp. n., ventral; k–l, P. odontiophallus sp. n., dorsal; m–n, P. eductus (Naudé), dorsal; o, P. exquadratus (Naudé), dorsal; p, P. tanyoplacus sp. n., dorsal; q, P. macropygeus sp. n., dorsal." pageId="10" pageNumber="11">4 f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="12" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1567,2004]" box="[196,1005,1679,1706]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,329,1679,1705]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Etymology</emphasis>
. Greek, for the plate (
<emphasis box="[588,664,1680,1705]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">plakos</emphasis>
) that is very short (
<emphasis box="[895,987,1680,1705]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">brachys</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1567,2004]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,407,1717,1743]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Male and female</emphasis>
. Yellowish ochraceous. Vertex with fuscous marking near ocellus, some fuscous spots on pronotum. Tegmina with fuscous lining mainly in inner anteapical, posterior discal and brachial cells (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="73.[151,255,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,194,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-70@73.[213,1373,194,1912]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURE 8 a–h. Pravistylus species. Habitus. a–b, P. bidentidiscus sp. n., a, male; b, female; c–d, P. brachyplacus sp. n., c, male; d, female; e, P. caenophallus sp. n., male; f–g, P. deltoplacus sp. n., male; h, P. dentidiscus sp. n., male." pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Figs 8 c</figureCitation>
, male, 8 d, female). Hind wing triangular, less than half length of tegmina.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1567,2004]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,259,1829,1855]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[274,419,1829,1855]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Dimensions</emphasis>
. (n = 8) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[519,608,1829,1855]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Length</emphasis>
: apex of vertex to apex of tegmina 2.0– 
<quantity box="[1073,1166,1829,1855]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
; apex of vertex to apex of abdomen 
<quantity box="[301,450,1866,1892]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="2.3" valueMax="2.4" valueMin="2.2">2.2–2.4 mm</quantity>
; vertex medially 
<quantity box="[658,754,1866,1892]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.4 mm</quantity>
; vertex next to eye 
<quantity box="[991,1087,1866,1892]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
; pronotum medially 
<quantity box="[1337,1432,1866,1892]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,230,1903,1929]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Width</emphasis>
: head 
<quantity box="[308,401,1904,1930]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
; pronotum 
<quantity box="[534,627,1904,1930]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
. Ocellar diameter 19.2–29.8 µm; ocellocular distance 42.0 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1567,2004]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1436,152,999]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="12" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,389,1941,1967]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Genital capsule</emphasis>
. Pygofer short; ventral posterior margin with small bulbous lobe; dorsal posterior margin subapically lobate (
<figureCitation box="[379,470,1978,2004]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="54.[151,258,1750,1774]" captionTargetBox="[187,1403,201,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-85@54.[180,1407,197,1753]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 1 a–l. Pravistylus species. Pygofer, laterally. a, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; b, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; c, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; d, P. caenophallus sp. n.; e, P. deltoplacus sp. n.; f–g, P. dentidiscus sp. n.; h, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; i–k, P.eductus(Naudé); l, P. exquadratus (Naudé)." pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 1 c</figureCitation>
). Pygofer lobe short, triangular, base about one third as wide as pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[1329,1420,1978,2004]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="54.[151,258,1750,1774]" captionTargetBox="[187,1403,201,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-85@54.[180,1407,197,1753]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 1 a–l. Pravistylus species. Pygofer, laterally. a, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; b, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; c, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; d, P. caenophallus sp. n.; e, P. deltoplacus sp. n.; f–g, P. dentidiscus sp. n.; h, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; i–k, P.eductus(Naudé); l, P. exquadratus (Naudé)." pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 1 c</figureCitation>
). Plate short, mediolateral margin right-angled; tufts of setae proximad and distad of angle; posterior margin truncate or slightly triangular; 3–4 submarginal macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[865,936,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="57.[151,255,1711,1735]" captionTargetBox="[198,1389,205,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-63@57.[190,1396,194,1718]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURE 2 a–i. Pravistylus species. Plate, part or whole structure. a, P. varicudiscus sp. n.; b, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; c, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; d, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; e–g, P.eductus(Naudé); h–i, P. exquadratus (Naudé)." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
aq); length 0.6–0.7 times as long as wide. Aedeagus, in lateral view, U-shaped; shaft short, parallel-sided, arising medially from atrium, in dorsal view slightly depressed; gonopore apical (
<figureCitation box="[612,713,264,290]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="62.[151,255,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[249,1353,187,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-126@62.[233,1361,182,1903]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 3 a–t. Pravistylus species. Aedeagus, laterally. a–b, P.lobus sp. n.; c, P. deltoplacussp. n.; d, P. mecophysis sp. n.; e, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; f, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; g, P. mollidiscus sp. n.; h, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; i–k, P. mutilidiscus sp. n.; l, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; m, P. odontiophallus sp. n.; n–o, P.eductus (Naudé); p–q, P. exquadratus (Naudé); r, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; s, P. macropygeus sp. n.; t, P. pollediscus sp. n." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs 3 f</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[728,766,264,290]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="64.[151,255,1673,1697]" captionTargetBox="[188,1400,199,1606]" captionTargetId="figure-144@64.[181,1405,194,1694]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURE 4 a–q. Pravistylus species. Aedeagus, dorsally or ventrally. a, P. lobus sp. n., dorsal; b, P. lobus sp. n., ventral; c, P. deltoplacus sp. n., dorsal; d, P. mecophysis sp. n., dorsal; e, P. bidentidiscus sp. n., dorsal; f, P. brachyplacus sp. n., dorsal; g, P. mollidiscus sp. n., dorsal; h, P. mecistoplacus sp. n., dorsal; i, P. mutilidiscus sp. n., dorsal; j, P. brachyphysis sp. n., ventral; k–l, P. odontiophallus sp. n., dorsal; m–n, P. eductus (Naudé), dorsal; o, P. exquadratus (Naudé), dorsal; p, P. tanyoplacus sp. n., dorsal; q, P. macropygeus sp. n., dorsal." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">4 f</figureCitation>
). Style distal part close to short anterior medial lobe; apophysis straight, tapering to blunt point; preapical lobe rounded; basal lateral lobe long; apophysis with one major ventral tooth as well as fine serration (
<figureCitation box="[686,792,338,364]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="66.[151,255,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[198,1391,200,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-128@66.[190,1397,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 5 a–p. Pravistylus species. Style, dorsally or ventrally. a–b, P. eductus (Naudé), ventral; c–d, P. exquadratus (Naudé), ventral; e, P. longitrunculus sp. n., ventral; f, P. mecistoplacus sp. n., ventral; g, P. mollidiscus sp. n., dorsal; h, P. scolopygeus sp. n., dorsal; i, P. serratus sp. n., dorsal; j, P. trunculidiscus sp. n., dorsal; k, P. bidentidiscus sp. n., dorsal; l, P. brachyphysis sp. n., dorsal; m, P. brachyplacus sp. n., dorsal; n, P. deltoplacus sp. n., ventral; o–p, P. dentidiscus sp. n., ventral." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[743,792,338,364]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="5.0">5 m</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). Connective in lateral view with stem slightly angled dorsally; in dorsal view, stem triangular, about 0.25 times as long as arms (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1120,376,402]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="69.[151,256,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[266,1320,198,1706]" captionTargetId="figure-273@69.[264,1329,194,1706]" captionTargetPageId="69" captionText="FIGURE 6 a–ai. Pravistylus species. Connective, dorsally or ventrally and laterally. a, P. lobus sp. n., ventral; b, P. deltoplacus sp. n., dorsal; c, P. mecophysis sp. n., dorsal; d, P. bidentidiscus sp. n., dorsal; e, P. brachyplacus sp. n., dorsal; f, P. mollidiscus sp. n., dorsal; g, P. mecistoplacus sp. n., dorsal; h, P. mutilidiscus sp. n., dorsal; i, P. brachyphysis sp. n., ventral; j, P. odontiophallus sp. n., dorsal; k, P. odontiophallus sp. n., ventral; l, P.eductus(Naudé), dorsal; m, P. eductus (Naudé), lateral; n–o, P. exquadratus (Naudé), dorsal; p, P. exquadratus (Naudé), lateral; q, P. tanyoplacus sp. n., dorsal; r, P. macropygeus sp. n., dorsal; s–u, P. pollediscus sp. n., dorsal; v, P. scolopygeus sp. n., dorsal; w, P. dentidiscus sp. n., dorsal; x, P. micropygeus sp. n., dorsal; y, P. trunculidiscus sp. n., dorsal; z, P. longitrunculus sp. n., dorsal; aa, P. digitidiscus sp. n., dorsal; ab, P. serratus sp. n., dorsal; ac, P. indistinctidiscus sp. n., dorsal; ad, P. odontopygeus sp. n., dorsal; ae, P. varicudiscus sp. n., ventral; af, P. pelorophallus sp. n., ventral; ag, P. pelorophallus sp. n., lateral; ah, P. scolophallus sp. n., ventral; ai, P. caenophallus sp. n., ventral." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 6 e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,152,999]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,287,413,439]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Female</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[302,447,413,439]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Dimensions</emphasis>
. (n = 14) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[566,655,413,439]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Length</emphasis>
: apex of vertex to apex of tegmina 
<quantity box="[1078,1223,413,439]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3499999999999996" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="2.3499999999999996" valueMax="2.4" valueMin="2.3">2.3–2.4 mm</quantity>
; apex of vertex to apex of abdomen 
<quantity box="[366,513,450,476]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="2.7" valueMax="2.9" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.9 mm</quantity>
; vertex medially 
<quantity box="[722,817,450,476]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
; vertex next to eye 
<quantity box="[1054,1149,450,476]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
; pronotum medially 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[211,290,487,513]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Width</emphasis>
: head 
<quantity box="[368,511,488,514]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="0.85" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.8">0.8–0.9 mm</quantity>
; pronotum 
<quantity box="[644,737,488,514]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
. Ocellar diameter 14.7–23.3 µm; ocellocular distance 39.3– 46.7 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,152,999]" box="[196,1340,562,588]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,319,562,588]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Sternite 7 base rectangular; posterior marginal ligula rounded, short, narrow (
<figureCitation box="[1232,1326,562,588]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="70.[151,255,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[228,1356,197,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-105@70.[225,1359,194,1900]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="FIGURE 7 a–af. Pravistylus species. Sternite 7 of female, whole structure, or posterior margin. a–b, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; c, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; d, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; e–f, P. caenophallus sp. n.; g–i, P. deltoplacus sp. n.; j–l, P. dentidiscus sp. n.; m–n, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; o–t, P. eductus (Naudé); u–w, P. exquadratus (Naudé); x–aa, P. indistinctidiscus sp. n.; ab–af, P. interdiscus sp. n." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 7 d</figureCitation>
