<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,152,999]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,312,749,775]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is distantly related to the other species with a short, tubular shaft with variable length, such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Stiller, 2010" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2010" box="[330,494,786,811]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pravistylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deltoplacus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[330,494,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. deltoplacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[500,566,786,812]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[500,566,786,812]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[582,673,786,812]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="62.[151,255,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[249,1353,187,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-126@62.[233,1361,182,1903]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 3 a–t. Pravistylus species. Aedeagus, laterally. a–b, P.lobus sp. n.; c, P. deltoplacussp. n.; d, P. mecophysis sp. n.; e, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; f, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; g, P. mollidiscus sp. n.; h, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; i–k, P. mutilidiscus sp. n.; l, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; m, P. odontiophallus sp. n.; n–o, P.eductus (Naudé); p–q, P. exquadratus (Naudé); r, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; s, P. macropygeus sp. n.; t, P. pollediscus sp. n." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 3 c</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Stiller, 2010" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2010" box="[695,858,786,811]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pravistylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mecophysis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[695,858,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. mecophysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[865,930,786,812]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[865,930,786,812]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[946,1039,786,812]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="62.[151,255,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[249,1353,187,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-126@62.[233,1361,182,1903]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 3 a–t. Pravistylus species. Aedeagus, laterally. a–b, P.lobus sp. n.; c, P. deltoplacussp. n.; d, P. mecophysis sp. n.; e, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; f, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; g, P. mollidiscus sp. n.; h, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; i–k, P. mutilidiscus sp. n.; l, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; m, P. odontiophallus sp. n.; n–o, P.eductus (Naudé); p–q, P. exquadratus (Naudé); r, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; s, P. macropygeus sp. n.; t, P. pollediscus sp. n." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 3 d</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2010" box="[1061,1244,786,811]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pravistylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bidentidiscus">
<emphasis box="[1061,1244,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. bidentidiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1260,1349,786,812]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="62.[151,255,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[249,1353,187,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-126@62.[233,1361,182,1903]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 3 a–t. Pravistylus species. Aedeagus, laterally. a–b, P.lobus sp. n.; c, P. deltoplacussp. n.; d, P. mecophysis sp. n.; e, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; f, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; g, P. mollidiscus sp. n.; h, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; i–k, P. mutilidiscus sp. n.; l, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; m, P. odontiophallus sp. n.; n–o, P.eductus (Naudé); p–q, P. exquadratus (Naudé); r, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; s, P. macropygeus sp. n.; t, P. pollediscus sp. n." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 3 e</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Stiller, 2010" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pravistylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mollidiscus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. mollidiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[292,358,823,849]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[292,358,823,849]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[373,466,824,850]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="62.[151,255,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[249,1353,187,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-126@62.[233,1361,182,1903]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 3 a–t. Pravistylus species. Aedeagus, laterally. a–b, P.lobus sp. n.; c, P. deltoplacussp. n.; d, P. mecophysis sp. n.; e, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; f, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; g, P. mollidiscus sp. n.; h, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; i–k, P. mutilidiscus sp. n.; l, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; m, P. odontiophallus sp. n.; n–o, P.eductus (Naudé); p–q, P. exquadratus (Naudé); r, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; s, P. macropygeus sp. n.; t, P. pollediscus sp. n." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[427,466,824,850]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="g" value="3.0">3 g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). The former three species have a short, tubular or somewhat depressed shaft, with the apex curved or angled dorsally, except in 
<taxonomicName authority="Stiller, 2010" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2010" box="[692,857,861,886]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pravistylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mollidiscus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[692,857,861,886]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. mollidiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[864,932,861,887]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[864,932,861,887]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
where the shaft is very thick and does not have the apex curved. No plate of any other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Theron" authorityYear="1975" box="[795,927,898,923]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pravistylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[795,927,898,923]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Pravistylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2010" box="[1164,1350,898,923]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pravistylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachyplacus">
<emphasis box="[1164,1350,898,923]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. brachyplacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1366,1436,898,924]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="57.[151,255,1711,1735]" captionTargetBox="[198,1389,205,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-63@57.[190,1396,194,1718]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURE 2 a–i. Pravistylus species. Plate, part or whole structure. a, P. varicudiscus sp. n.; b, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; c, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; d, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; e–g, P.eductus(Naudé); h–i, P. exquadratus (Naudé)." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
aq). The colour of this species (
<figureCitation box="[518,665,936,962]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="73.[151,255,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,194,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-70@73.[213,1373,194,1912]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURE 8 a–h. Pravistylus species. Habitus. a–b, P. bidentidiscus sp. n., a, male; b, female; c–d, P. brachyplacus sp. n., c, male; d, female; e, P. caenophallus sp. n., male; f–g, P. deltoplacus sp. n., male; h, P. dentidiscus sp. n., male." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs 8 c &amp; d</figureCitation>
) is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName box="[908,1025,936,961]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Deltocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eductus">
<emphasis box="[908,1025,936,961]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. eductus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1041,1229,936,962]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="73.[151,255,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,194,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-70@73.[213,1373,194,1912]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURE 8 a–h. Pravistylus species. Habitus. a–b, P. bidentidiscus sp. n., a, male; b, female; c–d, P. brachyplacus sp. n., c, male; d, female; e, P. caenophallus sp. n., male; f–g, P. deltoplacus sp. n., male; h, P. dentidiscus sp. n., male." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Figs 
<quantity box="[1100,1147,936,962]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="8.0">8 m</quantity>
, o &amp; q
</figureCitation>
). The short, blunt ligula of sternite 7 of the female (
<figureCitation box="[543,635,973,999]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="70.[151,255,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[228,1356,197,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-105@70.[225,1359,194,1900]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="FIGURE 7 a–af. Pravistylus species. Sternite 7 of female, whole structure, or posterior margin. a–b, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; c, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; d, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; e–f, P. caenophallus sp. n.; g–i, P. deltoplacus sp. n.; j–l, P. dentidiscus sp. n.; m–n, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; o–t, P. eductus (Naudé); u–w, P. exquadratus (Naudé); x–aa, P. indistinctidiscus sp. n.; ab–af, P. interdiscus sp. n." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 7 d</figureCitation>
) is unique within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Theron" authorityYear="1975" box="[847,979,973,998]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pravistylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[847,979,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Pravistylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
